<TITLE> Ex-MP Sakhawat detained for 'war crimes' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Jessore, June 22 (bdnews24.com)The police early on Monday arrested Jatiya Party leader and former MP Maolana Sakhawat Hossain at his house at Keshabpur in Jessore on war crimes charges. Sakhawat Jatiya Party presidium member and former Jamaat-e-Islami MP Maolana Sakhawat Hossain was kept under the custody of Kotwali police instead of Keshabpur police for security reasons. Jessore police superintendent Didar Ahmed told bdnews24.com that they had detained Sakhawat in a case filed by Sajjad Hossain Molla of the same upazila. Sajjad sued the Jatiya Party leader on charges of war crime during the independence war in 1971. Four cases have so far been filed against Sakhawat on charges of war crime, of which he was allowed bail in three cases, Didar said. bdn
